[This documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AGILE/Viewing+the+Control+Chart] about Control Chart has two problems that either make the explanation ambiguous or don't completely explain the problem:
# After some tests, it seems that the time spent in statuses only applies once the issue leaves the column in the board. This is an important information. I suggest adding the line in bold to this paragraph:
{quote}
For example, if you are using the JIRA Software Development workflow, you may consider work to have started on an issue when it transitions to 'In Progress' and work to have completed when it transitions out of 'In Review' (to 'Done'). You would show this on the Control Chart by selecting 'In Progress' and 'In Review' as the Columns, as that would show the time that issues have spent in those two statuses. *The time spent in each Columns is only updated once the issue has left it.*
{quote}
# The documentation uses a lot the term 'time spent', which in this case refers to time spent in columns, but in JIRA, this has another meaning, which is the time spent in worklogs. That makes the documentation misleading.

h3. Summary
Running JIRA Agile REST API in https://docs.atlassian.com/greenhopper/REST/6.7.7/#agile/1.0/ gives incorrect result 

h3. Environment
* JIRA 6.4.9
* JIRA Agile 6.7.7

h3. Steps to Reproduce
When running the below REST API command:
{code}
GET http://localhost:8649/rest/agile/1.0/issue/SCRUM-1
{code}

h3. Expected Results
It should return a single issue, for a given issue Id or issue key. Issues returned from this resource include Agile fields, like sprint, closedSprints, flagged, and epic.
*Example:*
{code}
